cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is related to computer vision and security, specifically in the area of person re-identification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of deep learning models for person re-ID also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for UAPs learning, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with surveillance systems, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
